  <worksheets>
    <worksheet name='Q1'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontname='Arial'> Explain the difference between a Tableau Dashboard and a Tableau Story Point. Give two healthcare-related use cases.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Arial'>Answer:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Dashboard:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'> A single screen with multiple charts used for interactive data analysis and monitoring. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Story Point:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'> A sequence of visuals used to present insights step-by-step like a story.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Example:- </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Dashboard: </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Monitor patient admissions, department workload, and treatment costs in real time. </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'>Story Point:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial'> Present a report showing patient trends, cost analysis, and regional insights to hospital management.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style>
          <style-rule element='header'>
            <format attr='width-header' value='52' />
          </style-rule>
        </style>
        <panes>
          <pane selection-relaxation-option='selection-relaxation-allow'>
            <view>
              <breakdown value='auto' />
            </view>
            <mark class='Automatic' />
          </pane>
        </panes>
        <rows />
        <cols />
      </table>
      <simple-id uuid='{51DF18C6-28D1-4C77-951B-E01309B6970D}' />
    </worksheet>
    <worksheet name='Q10'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>1. Which department generates the highest treatment cost?</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Answer:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>The department with the tallest bar in the </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11' italic='true'>Department Cost Chart</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> generates the highest treatment cost. i.e</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> Neurology(88,675).</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>2.Which region has more critical patients?</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Answer:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>South and West </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>has more critical patients </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>i.e 20</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>3. Business Decisions for Hospital Management:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Answer:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Allocate </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>more resources and staff</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> to high-demand departments and regions i.e Neurology for west region</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Focus on </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>cost control</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> in expensive departments i.e Neurology</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Improve </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>care quality</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> in regions with more critical patients i.e South and West.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>Plan </run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'>budget and infrastructure</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='11'> based on patient trends which is high in month of April and August</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style />
        <panes>
          <pane selection-relaxation-option='selection-relaxation-allow'>
            <view>
              <breakdown value='auto' />
            </view>
            <mark class='Automatic' />
          </pane>
        </panes>
        <rows />
        <cols />
      </table>
      <simple-id uuid='{C0C54A2A-3FEC-4269-B45D-EAF6F347CE3C}' />
    </worksheet>
    <worksheet name='Q2'>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'> What are Actions in Tableau? Explain how Filter Action can help hospital management analyze patient data.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>Answer:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>Actions in Tableau are interactive features that let users click or hover on one chart to affect another chart (e.g., filtering, highlighting, or navigating).</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>A Filter Action allows one visualization to filter data in another.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>Example:-</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>If hospital management clicks on a specific department (e.g., Cardiology). </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>All other charts update to show only Cardiology patients, costs, and trends.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>This helps management to:</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>1)Analyze department-wise patient data </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>2)Identify high-cost treatments in a specific department </run>
            <run>Æ&#10;</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Arial' fontsize='12'>3)Make better decisions quickly</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <table>
        <view>
          <datasources />
          <aggregation value='true' />
        </view>
        <style />
        <panes>
          <pane selection-relaxation-option='selection-relaxation-allow'>
            <view>
              <breakdown value='auto' />
            </view>
            <mark class='Automatic' />
          </pane>
        </panes>
        <rows />
        <cols />
      </table>
      <simple-id uuid='{EDEE6091-8E03-4233-8538-A766728AEF37}' />
    </worksheet>
